prefix_rule(pattern=["perl", "-0777", "-i", "", "-pe", "s/ALWAYS use \\*\\*semantic commit messages\\*\\* with \\[Conventional Commits\\]\\(https:\\/\\/www\\.conventionalcommits\\.org\\/\\) format: `<type>\\(<scope>\\): <description>`\\./ALWAYS use **semantic commit messages** with [Conventional Commits](https:\\/\\/www.conventionalcommits.org\\/) format: `<type>(<scope>): <gitmoji> <description>`./g; s/  - Examples: `feat\\(auth\\): add OAuth2 login flow`, `fix\\(api\\): resolve null pointer in response handler`, `docs\\(readme\\): update installation instructions`/  - Examples: `feat(auth): ✨ add OAuth2 login flow`, `fix(api): 🐛 resolve null pointer in response handler`, `docs(readme): 📝 update installation instructions`/g; s/- Do NOT use emojis or gitmoji in commit messages\\. Keep commit messages plain text only\\./- ALWAYS use gitmoji in commit messages. Put the gitmoji between scope and description./g", "__HOME__/.claude/CLAUDE.md"], decision="allow")
prefix_rule(pattern=["sed", "-i", "", "s|ALWAYS use \\*\\*semantic commit messages\\*\\* with \\[Conventional Commits\\](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`.|ALWAYS use **semantic commit messages** with [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) format: `<type>(<scope>): <gitmoji> <description>`.|", "__HOME__/.claude/CLAUDE.md"], decision="allow")
